description:
In crash_info_check_and_clear(), when crash_info.magic != CRASH_MAGIC (line 60-63), count is zeroed. However, if __noinit RAM contains garbage that happens to match CRASH_MAGIC (unlikely but possible), the code at line 51-59 will log the garbage values and clear reason/location/extra, but NOT reset count.

After the if-block completes, count retains whatever garbage value was in __noinit RAM. This is very unlikely (1 in 2^32 chance) but violates the invariant that count should be meaningful.

SEVERITY: P3 - extremely unlikely, but when it occurs, the count value will be wrong.

FIX: In the true branch (magic == CRASH_MAGIC), after logging, also clear count if we want count to represent 'crashes since last clear':
```c
if (crash_info.magic == CRASH_MAGIC) {
    LOG_WRN(...);
    crash_info.magic = 0;
    crash_info.reason = CRASH_NONE;
    crash_info.location = 0;
    crash_info.extra = 0;
    crash_info.count = 0;  // Also reset count
} else {
    crash_info.count = 0;
}
```

Or clarify if count is meant to persist across clears (accumulate across warm resets).
